regulated by this state; mechanical vibration or other physical 19
agent; waste, including materials that may be recycled, 20
reconditioned, or reclaimed; solid, liquid, gaseous, or thermal 21
irritant; or artificially produced electric field, magnetic 22
field, electromagnetic field, electromagnetic pulse, sound wave, 23
sound pollution, light pollution, microwave, or ionizing or non- 24
ionizing radiation. 25
(4) "Solar radiation modification" means an experiment in 26
the earth's climatic system involving the release of pollutants 27
that reduces the amount of sunlight absorbed by the earth, 28
including through marine cloud brightening, space-based 29
reflectors, or stratospheric aerosol injection. 30
(5) "Space-based reflectors" means deploying mirrors or 31
other reflective objects in space to deflect sunlight. 32
(6) "Stratospheric aerosol injection" means introducing 33
reflective particles into the stratosphere to reflect sunlight. 34
(B) No person or entity shall engage in solar radiation 35
modification, cloud seeding, or sunlight reflection methods in 36
this state, including through the use of an aircraft, balloon, 37
drone, space-based platform, or interoperable ground-based 38
facility. 39
(C) The superintendent of the state highway patrol or a 40
county sheriff shall issue a cease-and-desist order to a person 41
who the superintendent or sheriff determines is conducting or 42
attempting to conduct solar radiation modification, cloud 43
seeding, or sunlight reflection methods. No person shall fail to 44
comply with a cease and desist order issued under this division. 45
(D) A violation of this section is a strict liability 46
offense and section 2901.20 of the Revised Code does not apply. 47

